|YKOThe colorlist command displays the compact legacy color combinations
on DarkWind, plus a few expanded examples.  Here is how the color system
works:

Color codes are used by typing |<code> where you want the color to
begin and |000 where it should stop.  The spaces shown in examples like
"| XX0" are only there so the help text can show the code without
triggering it.

Legacy compact codes use three characters after the pipe: |XYZ.

The first character, X, is the foreground color.  Acceptable colors are:
  |RKBR   red|XX0
  |GKBG   green|XX0
  |BKBB   blue|XX0
  |KKBK   black|XX0
  |YKBY   yellow|XX0
  |CKBC   cyan|XX0
  |WKBW   white|XX0
  |MKBM   magenta|XX0

|YKOThe second character, Y, is the background color.  The acceptable
colors are the same as the foreground list.  X means no foreground or
background change.

The third character, Z, is the effect.
Acceptable options are:
  |YKBB   bold|XX0
  |YKUU   underscore|XX0
  |YKKK   blinking|XX0
  |YKO0   no affect

A few examples:
The code | XR0 produces |XR0This|XX0.
|YKOThe code | BYK produces |BYKThis|XX0.
|YKOThe code | GKB produces |GKBThis|XX0

Expanded color codes use bracketed markup:

  | [fg=<color>,bg=<color>,<effect>]text| 000

Remove the spaces after | when you use these codes.  They are included
here only so the help file can show the syntax.

Supported color values are:

  red, green, blue, black, yellow, cyan, white, magenta
  bright-red, bright-green, bright-blue, bright-black, bright-yellow,
  bright-cyan, bright-white, bright-magenta
  gray or grey
  ansi-0 through ansi-255
  xterm-0 through xterm-255
  #rrggbb truecolor hex values, such as #ff8800

Supported effects are:

  bold, italic, underline, underscore, blink, inverse, hidden,
  strikethrough, fraktur, double-underline, overline, reset, normal

Effects are comma-separated standalone tokens. For example, use blink as
an effect token, not as a background color:

  | [fg=#ff8800,bg=black,blink]blinking orange| 000

Expanded examples:

  | [fg=bright-cyan,bg=black,bold]bright cyan bold| 000
  | [fg=ansi-202,bg=black]xterm orange| 000
  | [fg=#ff8800,bg=black,underline]truecolor orange| 000
  | [fg=white,bg=black,bold,italic,overline]combined effects| 000

The color command accepts the same expanded color values for channel
foreground and background colors:

  color gossip bright-cyan black bold
  color gossip ansi-202 black none
  color gossip #ff8800 black underline
  color gossip white black italic
  color gossip bright-red black bold,italic

Darkflow and players using "set term modern" receive the richer colors.
Older ANSI terminals fall back to the nearest basic color.  Players with
color off see the text without the color markup.
